autoscale_alert.description: This alert config applies to auto scale alerts.

obj_uuid.description: UUID of the resource for which alert was raised.

threshold.description: An alert is created only when the number of events meets or exceeds this number within the chosen time frame. Allowed values are 1-65536.

throttle.description: Alerts are suppressed (throttled) for this duration of time since the last alert was raised for this alert config. Allowed values are 0-31536000.

category.description: Determines whether an alert is raised immediately when event occurs (realtime) or after specified number of events occurs within rolling time window. Enum options - REALTIME, ROLLINGWINDOW, WATERMARK.

_last_modified.description: UNIX time since epoch in microseconds. Units(MICROSECONDS).

expiry_time.description: An alert is expired and deleted after the expiry time has elapsed.  The original event triggering the alert remains in the event's log. Allowed values are 1-31536000.

uuid.description: Unique object identifier of the object.

tenant_ref.description: It is a reference to an object of type Tenant.

summary.description: Summary of reason why alert is generated.

rolling_window.description: Only if the Number of Events is reached or exceeded within the Time Window will an alert be generated. Allowed values are 1-31536000.

source.description: Signifies system events or the type of client logsused in this alert configuration. Enum options - CONN_LOGS, APP_LOGS, EVENT_LOGS, METRICS.

alert_rule.description: list of filters matching on events or client logs used for triggering alerts.

action_group_ref.description: The alert config will trigger the selected alert action, which can send notifications and execute a controlscript. It is a reference to an object of type ActionGroupConfig.

comparator.description: Enum options - ALERT_OP_LT, ALERT_OP_LE, ALERT_OP_EQ, ALERT_OP_NE, ALERT_OP_GE, ALERT_OP_GT.
